{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895019914,"sessionID":"ses_28468ce19ffebZjIwGuVArSMoW","part":{"id":"prt_d7b977cbf001qPUrdYn1ILnfNw","messageID":"msg_d7b975dcb001BiMvJ8kFS9BRq3","sessionID":"ses_28468ce19ffebZjIwGuVArSMoW","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_functions.glob:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z","pattern":"cmd/**/*"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md","metadata":{"count":1,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z","time":{"start":1775895019898,"end":1775895019912}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895019923,"sessionID":"ses_28468ce19ffebZjIwGuVArSMoW","part":{"id":"prt_d7b97777c001j6pmqqpsmWgmLk","messageID":"msg_d7b975dcb001BiMvJ8kFS9BRq3","sessionID":"ses_28468ce19ffebZjIwGuVArSMoW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status е‘Ҫд»Ө вҖ” Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document provides technical implementation details for the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands for the AgentCube project. These commands enable users to interact with deployed agents and check their deployment status.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-023  \n8: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n9: **Language:** Python  \n10: **Size:** M\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### Component Diagram\n17: \n18: ```\n19: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n20: в”Ӯ                              CLI Layer                                        в”Ӯ\n21: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                         в”Ӯ\n22: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   invoke command    в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   status command    в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\n23: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   (main.py:379)     в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   (main.py:409)     в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\n24: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                         в”Ӯ\n25: в”Ӯ             в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                     в”Ӯ\n26: в”Ӯ             в–ј                          в–ј                                     в”Ӯ\n27: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                         в”Ӯ\n28: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   InvokeRuntime     в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   StatusRuntime     в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\n29: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   (invoke_runtime)  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   (status_runtime)  в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\n30: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                         в”Ӯ\n31: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n32:               в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ\n33:               в–ј                          в–ј\n34: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n35: в”Ӯ                           Service Layer                                       в”Ӯ\n36: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\n37: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  MetadataService    в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ AgentCubeProvider   в”Ӯ    в”ӮKubernetesProviderв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n38: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  (load metadata)    в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ  (CR operations)    в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ (K8s resources)  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n39: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\n40: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n41:               в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                        в”Ӯ\n42:               в–ј                          в–ј                        в–ј\n43: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n44: в”Ӯ                           External APIs                                       в”Ӯ\n45: в”Ӯ       Agent Metadata YAML         AgentRuntime CR           K8s API         в”Ӯ\n46: в”Ӯ     (agent_metadata.yaml)    (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)  (Deployment)   в”Ӯ\n47: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Data Flow\n51: \n52: #### Invoke Command Flow\n53: ```\n54: 1. CLI parses arguments (workspace, payload, headers, provider)\n55: 2. Validate payload is valid JSON\n56: 3. Parse header strings into dict (format: \"key:value\")\n57: 4. InvokeRuntime.invoke():\n58:    a. Load metadata from workspace\n59:    b. Validate prerequisites (agent_id for agentcube, endpoint for k8s)\n60:    c. Determine endpoint URL based on provider\n61:    d. Add session header if session_id exists in metadata\n62:    e. Send HTTP POST with payload\n63:    f. Return response\n64: 5. CLI formats and displays result\n65: ```\n66: \n67: #### Status Command Flow\n68: ```\n69: 1. CLI parses arguments (workspace, provider)\n70: 2. StatusRuntime.get_status():\n71:    a. Load metadata from workspace\n72:    b. If no agent_id вҶ’ return \"not_published\"\n73:    c. Based on provider:\n74:       - agentcube: Query AgentRuntime CR status\n75:       - k8s: Query Deployment/Service status\n76:    d. Return status dict\n77: 3. CLI displays status in Rich Table\n78: 4. Exit code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\"\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## Module Structure\n84: \n85: ### File Layout\n86: \n87: | Path | Role |\n88: |------|------|\n89: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke()` and `status()` commands (lines 379-430) |\n90: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` class for agent invocation |\n91: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` class for status checking |\n92: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for loading/saving metadata |\n93: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for CR operations |\n94: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for K8s resource operations |\n95: \n96: ### Dependencies\n97: \n98: ```\n99: invoke/status commands\n100:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ InvokeRuntime / StatusRuntime\n101:     в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ MetadataService\n102:     в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ AgentMetadata (Pydantic model)\n103:     в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ AgentCubeProvider (if provider=agentcube)\n104:     в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ Kubernetes client (custom resources)\n105:     в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ KubernetesProvider (if provider=k8s)\n106:     в”Ӯ               в””в”Җв”Җ Kubernetes client (Deployment/Service)\n107:     в””в”Җв”Җ httpx (for HTTP requests in invoke)\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Implementation Details\n113: \n114: ### 1. CLI Commands (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n115: \n116: #### Invoke Command\n117: \n118: ```python\n119: @app.command()\n120: def invoke(\n121:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n122:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n123:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n124:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n125:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n126: ) -> None:\n127: ```\n128: \n129: **Implementation Logic:**\n130: \n131: ```python\n132: def invoke(...) -> None:\n133:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n134:     \n135:     # 1. Validate JSON payload\n136:     try:\n137:         payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n138:     except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n139:         console.print(f\"Error: Invalid JSON payload - {e}\", style=\"red\")\n140:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n141:     \n142:     # 2. Parse headers\n143:     headers = {}\n144:     if header_list:\n145:         for header in header_list:\n146:             if \":\" not in header:\n147:                 console.print(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\", style=\"red\")\n148:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n149:             key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n150:             headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n151:     \n152:     # 3. Create runtime and invoke\n153:     runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n154:     \n155:     try:\n156:         with Progress(...) as progress:\n157:             task = progress.add_task(\"Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n158:             result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)\n159:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n160:         \n161:         # 4. Display result\n162:         console.print(\"[green]вң“[/green] Agent invoked successfully!\")\n163:         console.print_json(data=result)\n164:         \n165:     except Exception as e:\n166:         _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### Status Command\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: @app.command()\n173: def status(\n174:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n175:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n176:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n177: ) -> None:\n178: ```\n179: \n180: **Implementation Logic:**\n181: \n182: ```python\n183: def status(...) -> None:\n184:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n185:     \n186:     runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n187:     \n188:     try:\n189:         status_result = runtime.get_status(workspace_path)\n190:         \n191:         # Display in Rich Table\n192:         table = Table(title=\"Agent Status\")\n193:         table.add_column(\"Property\", style=\"cyan\")\n194:         table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n195:         \n196:         for key, value in status_result.items():\n197:             table.add_row(key, str(value))\n198:         \n199:         console.print(table)\n200:         \n201:         # Exit with code 1 if not published or error\n202:         if status_result.get(\"status\") in (\"not_published\", \"error\"):\n203:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n204:             \n205:     except Exception as e:\n206:         _handle_error(e, \"checking status\", verbose)\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ### 2. InvokeRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n212: \n213: #### Class Definition\n214: \n215: ```python\n216: class InvokeRuntime:\n217:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n218:     \n219:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n220:         self.verbose = verbose\n221:         self.provider = provider\n222:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n223:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n224:     \n225:     def invoke(\n226:         self,\n227:         workspace_path: Path,\n228:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n229:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n230:     ) -> Any:\n231:         \"\"\"Invoke the agent.\"\"\"\n232:         headers = headers or {}\n233:         \n234:         # Validate prerequisites and get metadata\n235:         metadata, endpoint, agent_id = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n236:         \n237:         # Add session header if available\n238:         if metadata.session_id:\n239:             headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n240:         \n241:         # Invoke based on provider\n242:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n243:             return self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path)\n244:         else:\n245:             return self._direct_http_invocation(endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path)\n246: ```\n247: \n248: #### Key Methods\n249: \n250: **`_validate_invoke_prerequisites`**\n251: ```python\n252: def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n253:     \"\"\"Validate that the agent can be invoked.\n254:     \n255:     Returns:\n256:         Tuple of (metadata, endpoint, agent_id)\n257:     \n258:     Raises:\n259:         ValueError: If metadata is missing required fields.\n260:     \"\"\"\n261:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n262:     \n263:     if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n264:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n265:             raise ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\")\n266:         if not metadata.router_url:\n267:             raise ValueError(\"router_url is required in metadata for agentcube provider\")\n268:         endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint or metadata.router_url\n269:         return metadata, endpoint, metadata.agent_id\n270:     else:\n271:         # k8s provider\n272:         if not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n273:             raise ValueError(\"No Kubernetes deployment found. Run 'publish --provider k8s' first.\")\n274:         endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint or self._build_k8s_endpoint(metadata)\n275:         return metadata, endpoint, metadata.agent_name\n276: ```\n277: \n278: **`_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`**\n279: ```python\n280: async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n281:     self,\n282:     agent_id: str,\n283:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n284:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n285:     endpoint: str,\n286:     workspace_path: Path,\n287: ) -> Any:\n288:     \"\"\"Invoke agent through AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR).\n289:     \n290:     For AgentRuntime CR deployments, rewrites URL to:\n291:     {base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n292:     \"\"\"\n293:     import httpx\n294:     \n295:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n296:     \n297:     # Build invocation URL\n298:     if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n299:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n300:         agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n301:         base_url = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n302:         invoke_url = f\"{base_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n303:     else:\n304:         invoke_url = endpoint\n305:     \n306:     # Make request\n307:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n308:         response = await client.post(\n309:             invoke_url,\n310:             json=payload,\n311:             headers=headers,\n312:             timeout=30.0,\n313:         )\n314:         response.raise_for_status()\n315:         return response.json()\n316: ```\n317: \n318: **`_direct_http_invocation`**\n319: ```python\n320: async def _direct_http_invocation(\n321:     self,\n322:     endpoint: str,\n323:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n324:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n325:     workspace_path: Path,\n326: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n327:     \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments.\"\"\"\n328:     import httpx\n329:     \n330:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n331:         response = await client.post(\n332:             endpoint,\n333:             json=payload,\n334:             headers=headers,\n335:             timeout=30.0,\n336:         )\n337:         response.raise_for_status()\n338:         return response.json()\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### 3. StatusRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n344: \n345: #### Class Definition\n346: \n347: ```python\n348: class StatusRuntime:\n349:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for checking agent status.\"\"\"\n350:     \n351:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n352:         self.verbose = verbose\n353:         self.provider = provider\n354:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n355:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n356:     \n357:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n358:         \"\"\"Get the agent status.\n359:         \n360:         Returns:\n361:             Dict with keys:\n362:             - status: \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\", \"not_published\", etc.\n363:             - agent_name: The agent name\n364:             - agent_id: The agent ID (if published)\n365:             - endpoint: The agent endpoint (if available)\n366:             - provider: The provider used\n367:             - message: Human-readable status message\n368:         \"\"\"\n369:         provider = provider or self.provider\n370:         \n371:         try:\n372:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n373:         except FileNotFoundError:\n374:             return {\n375:                 \"status\": \"error\",\n376:                 \"message\": f\"No metadata found in {workspace_path}\",\n377:             }\n378:         \n379:         # Check if published\n380:         if not metadata.agent_id and not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n381:             return {\n382:                 \"status\": \"not_published\",\n383:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n384:                 \"message\": \"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\",\n385:             }\n386:         \n387:         # Get status based on provider\n388:         if provider == \"agentcube\":\n389:             return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n390:         else:\n391:             return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n392: ```\n393: \n394: #### Key Methods\n395: \n396: **`_get_k8s_status`**\n397: ```python\n398: def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n399:     \"\"\"Get status for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n400:     from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n401:     \n402:     if not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n403:         return {\n404:             \"status\": \"error\",\n405:             \"message\": \"No Kubernetes deployment information found\",\n406:         }\n407:     \n408:     k8s = KubernetesProvider(\n409:         namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n410:         verbose=self.verbose,\n411:     )\n412:     \n413:     try:\n414:         agent_status = k8s.get_agent_status(metadata.k8s_deployment[\"name\"])\n415:         return {\n416:             \"status\": agent_status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n417:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n418:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n419:             \"endpoint\": metadata.agent_endpoint,\n420:             \"provider\": \"k8s\",\n421:             \"deployment\": metadata.k8s_deployment,\n422:             \"message\": f\"Deployment is {agent_status.get('status', 'unknown')}\",\n423:         }\n424:     except Exception as e:\n425:         return {\n426:             \"status\": \"error\",\n427:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n428:             \"message\": f\"Failed to get status: {e}\",\n429:         }\n430: ```\n431: \n432: **`_get_cr_k8s_status`**\n433: ```python\n434: def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n435:     \"\"\"Get status for AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n436:     from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n437:     \n438:     if not metadata.agent_id:\n439:         return {\n440:             \"status\": \"not_published\",\n441:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n442:             \"message\": \"Agent has not been published\",\n443:         }\n444:     \n445:     namespace = \"default\"\n446:     if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n447:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n448:     \n449:     provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n450:     \n451:     try:\n452:         cr = provider.get_agent_runtime(metadata.agent_name, namespace)\n453:         \n454:         if cr is None:\n455:             return {\n456:                 \"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\",\n457:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n458:                 \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n459:                 \"message\": \"AgentRuntime CR not found in Kubernetes\",\n460:             }\n461:         \n462:         # Extract status from CR\n463:         cr_status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n464:         if cr_status:\n465:             status = cr_status.get(\"status\", \"created_no_status\")\n466:             endpoint = cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\") or metadata.agent_endpoint\n467:         else:\n468:             status = \"created_no_status\"\n469:             endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint\n470:         \n471:         return {\n472:             \"status\": status,\n473:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n474:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n475:             \"endpoint\": endpoint,\n476:             \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n477:             \"message\": f\"AgentRuntime is {status}\",\n478:         }\n479:         \n480:     except Exception as e:\n481:         return {\n482:             \"status\": \"error\",\n483:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n484:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n485:             \"message\": f\"Failed to get status: {e}\",\n486:         }\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ### 4. Service Provider Integration\n492: \n493: #### AgentCubeProvider (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n494: \n495: The `AgentCubeProvider` provides access to the AgentRuntime CR:\n496: \n497: ```python\n498: class AgentCubeProvider:\n499:     \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n500:     \n501:     CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n502:     CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n503:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n504:     \n505:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n506:         \"\"\"Get an AgentRuntime CR by name.\n507:         \n508:         Returns:\n509:             The CR dict if found, None otherwise.\n510:         \"\"\"\n511:         try:\n512:             cr = self.custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n513:                 group=self.CR_GROUP,\n514:                 version=self.CR_VERSION,\n515:                 namespace=namespace,\n516:                 plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n517:                 name=name,\n518:             )\n519:             return cr\n520:         except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n521:             if e.status == 404:\n522:                 return None\n523:             raise\n524: ```\n525: \n526: #### KubernetesProvider (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n527: \n528: The `KubernetesProvider` provides access to standard K8s resources:\n529: \n530: ```python\n531: class KubernetesProvider:\n532:     \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service operations.\"\"\"\n533:     \n534:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n535:         \"\"\"Get status of the agent deployment.\n536:         \n537:         Returns:\n538:             Dict with status info including:\n539:             - status: \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\"\n540:             - replicas: number of replicas\n541:             - available_replicas: number of available replicas\n542:         \"\"\"\n543:         try:\n544:             deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(\n545:                 name=self._sanitize_name(agent_name),\n546:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n547:             )\n548:             \n549:             status = deployment.status\n550:             available = status.available_replicas or 0\n551:             desired = status.replicas or 0\n552:             \n553:             if available == desired and desired > 0:\n554:                 state = \"ready\"\n555:             elif available < desired:\n556:                 state = \"pending\"\n557:             else:\n558:                 state = \"error\"\n559:             \n560:             return {\n561:                 \"status\": state,\n562:                 \"replicas\": desired,\n563:                 \"available_replicas\": available,\n564:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n565:             }\n566:             \n567:         except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n568:             if e.status == 404:\n569:                 return {\"status\": \"not_found\"}\n570:             raise\n571: ```\n572: \n573: ---\n574: \n575: ## Data Models\n576: \n577: ### AgentMetadata (Relevant Fields)\n578: \n579: | Field | Type | Used In |\n580: |-------|------|---------|\n581: | `agent_name` | `str` | invoke, status |\n582: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | invoke, status (published check) |\n583: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (header) |\n584: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (endpoint) |\n585: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (endpoint fallback) |\n586: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict]` | status (provider selection) |\n587: \n588: ### Status Response Schema\n589: \n590: ```python\n591: {\n592:     \"status\": str,  # \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\", \"not_published\", \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"created_no_status\"\n593:     \"agent_name\": str,\n594:     \"agent_id\": Optional[str],\n595:     \"endpoint\": Optional[str],\n596:     \"provider\": str,  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n597:     \"message\": str,\n598:     # For k8s provider:\n599:     \"deployment\": Optional[Dict[str, Any]],\n600:     # For agentcube provider:\n601:     # Additional CR status fields\n602: }\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ---\n606: \n607: ## Error Handling\n608: \n609: ### Error Patterns\n610: \n611: All errors are handled via `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n612: \n613: ```python\n614: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n615:     console.print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", style=\"red\")\n616:     if verbose:\n617:         console.print_exception()\n618:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n619: ```\n620: \n621: ### Specific Error Cases\n622: \n623: | Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n624: |----------|------------|---------|\n625: | Invalid JSON payload | `json.JSONDecodeError` | \"Invalid JSON payload - {details}\" |\n626: | Invalid header format | `typer.Exit(1)` | \"Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\" |\n627: | Agent not published | `ValueError` | \"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\" |\n628: | Missing router_url | `ValueError` | \"router_url is required in metadata for agentcube provider\" |\n629: | No K8s deployment | `ValueError` | \"No Kubernetes deployment found...\" |\n630: | HTTP error | `httpx.HTTPStatusError` | propagated with status code |\n631: | K8s API error | `kubernetes.client.ApiException` | propagated |\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## Configuration\n636: \n637: ### Environment Variables\n638: \n639: The invoke command respects these environment variables (via metadata):\n640: \n641: | Variable | Used For |\n642: |----------|----------|\n643: | `ROUTER_URL` | Default router URL if not in metadata |\n644: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload manager for AgentCube provider |\n645: \n646: ### Metadata File Resolution\n647: \n648: The `MetadataService` loads metadata in this order:\n649: 1. `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n650: 2. `{workspace}/agent.yaml` (fallback)\n651: 3. `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n652: \n653: ---\n654: \n655: ## Testing Strategy\n656: \n657: ### Unit Tests\n658: \n659: 1. **InvokeRuntime tests**:\n660:    - Payload validation\n661:    - Header parsing\n662:    - Endpoint URL construction\n663:    - Session header injection\n664:    - Error handling\n665: \n666: 2. **StatusRuntime tests**:\n667:    - Status extraction from CR\n668:    - Status extraction from Deployment\n669:    - Not published detection\n670:    - Error state handling\n671: \n672: ### Integration Tests\n673: \n674: 1. **Invoke command E2E**:\n675:    - Invoke with JSON payload\n676:    - Invoke with custom headers\n677:    - Invoke against both providers\n678: \n679: 2. **Status command E2E**:\n680:    - Status for published agent\n681:    - Status for unpublished agent (exit code 1)\n682:    - Status for error state (exit code 1)\n683: \n684: ---\n685: \n686: ## Security Considerations\n687: \n688: 1. **Header handling**: Headers are parsed carefully to prevent injection attacks\n689: 2. **No secrets in logs**: Verbose mode does not log sensitive headers\n690: 3. **HTTPS preferred**: Endpoint URLs should use HTTPS in production\n691: 4. **K8s RBAC**: Status checks require appropriate K8s permissions\n692: \n693: ---\n694: \n695: ## Future Enhancements\n696: \n697: 1. **WebSocket support**: Real-time status updates\n698: 2. **Log streaming**: Stream agent logs during invocation\n699: 3. **Retry logic**: Automatic retry with exponential backoff\n700: 4. **Batch invoke**: Invoke multiple agents in parallel\n701: 5. **Output templating**: Custom output format templates\n702: \n703: ---\n704: \n705: ## References\n706: \n707: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n708: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n709: - [AgentCube Python SDK](../../python-sdk/design.md) - SDK design patterns\n710: - [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md) - CR API details\n\n(End of file - total 710 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status е‘Ҫд»Ө вҖ” Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands for the AgentCube project. These commands enable users to interact with deployed agents and check their deployment status.\n\n**AR:** AR-023  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                              CLI Layer                                        в”Ӯ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775895019894,"end":1775895019920}}}}
