{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895394326,"sessionID":"ses_28468ce19ffebZjIwGuVArSMoW","part":{"id":"prt_d7b981d64001z49KfZJvTfQTk5","messageID":"msg_d7b97dc38001MtUf2fb7EOAP95","sessionID":"ses_28468ce19ffebZjIwGuVArSMoW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","content":"# AR-024: DockerService Encapsulation вҖ” Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `DockerService` component in the AgentCube CLI project. The DockerService provides a high-level abstraction over the Docker SDK for building, managing, and publishing container images.\n\n**AR:** AR-024  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                            CLI Layer                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   build command     в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   publish command   в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   (main.py)         в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   (main.py)         в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ             в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                     в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ             в–ј                          в–ј                                     в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   BuildRuntime      в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   PublishRuntime    в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   (build_runtime)   в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   (publish_runtime) в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                         в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ\n              в–ј                          в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                          Service Layer                                        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                                    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                    в”Ӯ    DockerService    в”Ӯ                                    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                    в”Ӯ   (docker_service)  в”Ӯ                                    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                                    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                               в”Ӯ                                               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в–ј                в–ј                в–ј                              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в”Ӯ  Build Image    в”Ӯ в”Ӯ Push Image  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  Remove Image в”Ӯ                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ             в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                              в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ\n              в–ј                 в–ј                в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                         Docker Engine API                                     в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                    (docker.from_env() SDK)                                   в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n#### Build Image Flow\n```\n1. BuildRuntime calls DockerService.build_image()\n2. DockerService validates Docker is available\n3. Calls Docker SDK to build image from Dockerfile\n4. Streams build logs (if verbose)\n5. Returns image info (name, id, size, build_time)\n```\n\n#### Push Image Flow\n```\n1. PublishRuntime calls DockerService.push_image()\n2. If credentials provided, login to registry\n3. Tag image for target registry (if needed)\n4. Push image with streaming logs\n5. Return push confirmation with timestamp\n```\n\n#### Remove Image Flow\n```\n1. BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime calls DockerService.remove_image()\n2. Attempt to remove image by name\n3. Return True on success, False on failure\n4. Log warning on failure (non-blocking)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Module Structure\n\n### File Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` class - Docker SDK wrapper |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package marker |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService for image building |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService for image pushing |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```\nDockerService\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ docker (Docker SDK for Python)\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ pathlib (Path handling)\n    в””в”Җв”Җ typing (Type hints)\n\nBuildRuntime\n    в””в”Җв”Җ DockerService (for local builds)\n\nPublishRuntime\n    в””в”Җв”Җ DockerService (for image preparation and push)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. DockerService (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n\n#### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service class for Docker operations.\n    \n    Provides high-level abstraction over Docker SDK for:\n    - Image building from Dockerfiles\n    - Image inspection and information retrieval\n    - Image pushing to registries\n    - Image cleanup/removal\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n    \n    @property\n    def client(self) -> docker.DockerClient:\n        \"\"\"Lazy initialization of Docker client.\"\"\"\n        if self._client is None:\n            self._client = docker.from_env()\n        return self._client\n```\n\n#### Key Methods\n\n**`check_docker_available`**\n```python\ndef check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if Docker daemon is accessible.\n    \n    Returns:\n        True if Docker is available, False otherwise.\n        \n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If Docker is not available (when used in build context).\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        self.client.ping()\n        return True\n    except docker.errors.DockerException as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Docker is not available: {e}\")\n        return False\n```\n\n**`build_image`**\n```python\ndef build_image(\n    self,\n    dockerfile_path: Path,\n    context_path: Path,\n    image_name: str,\n    tag: str = \"latest\",\n    build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\n    \n    Args:\n        dockerfile_path: Path to the Dockerfile\n        context_path: Build context directory\n        image_name: Name for the built image\n        tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n        build_args: Optional build arguments\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n        - image_name: Full image name with tag\n        - image_id: Docker image ID\n        - image_size: Human-readable image size\n        - build_time: ISO format timestamp\n        \n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If Docker is unavailable or build fails\n        docker.errors.BuildError: If image build fails\n    \"\"\"\n    if not self.check_docker_available():\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n    \n    build_args = build_args or {}\n    full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n    \n    self.logger.info(f\"Building image: {full_image_name}\")\n    self.logger.debug(f\"Dockerfile: {dockerfile_path}\")\n    self.logger.debug(f\"Context: {context_path}\")\n    self.logger.debug(f\"Build args: {build_args}\")\n    \n    start_time = datetime.now()\n    \n    try:\n        # Build the image with streaming logs\n        image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n            path=str(context_path),\n            dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path.relative_to(context_path)),\n            tag=full_image_name,\n            buildargs=build_args,\n            rm=True,\n            forcerm=True,\n        )\n        \n        # Stream logs if verbose\n        if self.verbose:\n            for log_line in build_logs:\n                if 'stream' in log_line:\n                    self.logger.debug(log_line['stream'].strip())\n        \n        build_time = (datetime.now() - start_time).total_seconds()\n        \n        # Get image info\n        image_info = self._get_image_info(full_image_name)\n        \n        self.logger.info(f\"Successfully built {full_image_name} in {build_time:.2f}s\")\n        \n        return {\n            \"image_name\": full_image_name,\n            \"image_id\": image.id,\n            \"image_size\": image_info.get(\"size\", \"unknown\"),\n            \"build_time\": f\"{build_time:.2f}s\",\n        }\n        \n    except docker.errors.BuildError as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Build failed: {e}\")\n        # Log build output for debugging\n        if self.verbose and hasattr(e, 'build_log'):\n            for log in e.build_log:\n                if 'error' in log:\n                    self.logger.error(log['error'])\n        raise\n```\n\n**`get_image_info`**\n```python\ndef get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Name of the image (with optional tag)\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n        - id: Image ID\n        - size: Human-readable size\n        - created: Creation timestamp\n        - tags: List of image tags\n        \n    Raises:\n        docker.errors.ImageNotFound: If image doesn't exist\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n        return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n    except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n        self.logger.warning(f\"Image not found: {image_name}\")\n        raise\n```\n\n**`_get_image_info` (internal)**\n```python\ndef _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Internal method to extract image information.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Name of the image\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dict with image details\n    \"\"\"\n    image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n    \n    # Extract size from image attrs\n    size_bytes = image.attrs.get('Size', 0)\n    \n    return {\n        \"id\": image.id,\n        \"size\": self._format_size(size_bytes),\n        \"created\": image.attrs.get('Created', 'unknown'),\n        \"tags\": image.tags,\n    }\n```\n\n**`_format_size` (internal)**\n```python\ndef _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Format byte size to human-readable string.\n    \n    Args:\n        size_bytes: Size in bytes\n        \n    Returns:\n        Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.5 MB\")\n    \"\"\"\n    for unit in ['B', 'KB', 'MB', 'GB', 'TB']:\n        if size_bytes < 1024.0:\n            return f\"{size_bytes:.1f} {unit}\"\n        size_bytes /= 1024.0\n    return f\"{size_bytes:.1f} PB\"\n```\n\n**`push_image`**\n```python\ndef push_image(\n    self,\n    image_name: str,\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    username: Optional[str] = None,\n    password: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Name of the local image\n        registry_url: Target registry URL (e.g., \"registry.example.com\")\n        username: Registry username (optional)\n        password: Registry password (optional)\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n        - pushed_image: Full image name in registry\n        - push_time: ISO format timestamp\n        - registry: Registry URL used\n        \n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If push fails\n        docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API returns error\n    \"\"\"\n    if not self.check_docker_available():\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n    \n    self.logger.info(f\"Pushing image: {image_name}\")\n    \n    # Login if credentials provided\n    if username and password and registry_url:\n        self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n    \n    # Determine target image name\n    if registry_url:\n        # Tag for target registry\n        target_image = f\"{registry_url.rstrip('/')}/{image_name}\"\n        self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target_image)\n    else:\n        target_image = image_name\n    \n    start_time = datetime.now()\n    \n    try:\n        # Push with streaming logs\n        push_logs = self.client.images.push(target_image, stream=True, decode=True)\n        \n        if self.verbose:\n            for log_line in push_logs:\n                if 'status' in log_line:\n                    self.logger.debug(log_line['status'])\n                if 'error' in log_line:\n                    raise RuntimeError(f\"Push failed: {log_line['error']}\")\n        \n        push_time = (datetime.now() - start_time).total_seconds()\n        \n        self.logger.info(f\"Successfully pushed {target_image} in {push_time:.2f}s\")\n        \n        return {\n            \"pushed_image\": target_image,\n            \"push_time\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n            \"registry\": registry_url or \"docker.io\",\n        }\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Push failed: {e}\")\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push image: {e}\")\n```\n\n**`_docker_login_sdk` (internal)**\n```python\ndef _docker_login_sdk(\n    self,\n    registry: Optional[str],\n    username: str,\n    password: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Login to Docker registry using SDK.\n    \n    Args:\n        registry: Registry URL (None for Docker Hub)\n        username: Registry username\n        password: Registry password\n    \"\"\"\n    self.logger.debug(f\"Logging in to registry: {registry or 'docker.io'}\")\n    \n    try:\n        self.client.login(\n            username=username,\n            password=password,\n            registry=registry,\n        )\n        self.logger.debug(\"Login successful\")\n    except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Login failed: {e}\")\n        raise\n```\n\n**`_tag_image_sdk` (internal)**\n```python\ndef _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Tag an image for a different registry/repository.\n    \n    Args:\n        source_image: Original image name\n        target_image: Target image name\n    \"\"\"\n    self.logger.debug(f\"Tagging {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n    \n    image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n    \n    # Parse target image for repo:tag format\n    if ':' in target_image:\n        repo, tag = target_image.rsplit(':', 1)\n    else:\n        repo, tag = target_image, \"latest\"\n    \n    image.tag(repository=repo, tag=tag)\n    self.logger.debug(f\"Tagged successfully\")\n```\n\n**`remove_image`**\n```python\ndef remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Name of the image to remove\n        \n    Returns:\n        True if removal succeeded, False otherwise\n        \n    Note:\n        This method is non-blocking - failures are logged as warnings\n        but not raised as exceptions.\n    \"\"\"\n    self.logger.info(f\"Removing image: {image_name}\")\n    \n    try:\n        self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=False, noprune=False)\n        self.logger.info(f\"Successfully removed {image_name}\")\n        return True\n        \n    except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n        self.logger.warning(f\"Image not found (may already be removed): {image_name}\")\n        return True  # Consider it success if already gone\n        \n    except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n        self.logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n        return False\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. BuildRuntime Integration\n\nThe `BuildRuntime` uses `DockerService` for local image builds:\n\n```python\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for building agent images.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n    \n    def _build_local(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        options: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Build image locally using Docker.\"\"\"\n        # Validate Docker is available\n        if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n        \n        # Get Dockerfile path\n        dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found. Run 'pack' first.\")\n        \n        # Prepare build arguments\n        build_args = {}\n        if options.get(\"proxy\"):\n            build_args[\"HTTP_PROXY\"] = options[\"proxy\"]\n            build_args[\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] = options[\"proxy\"]\n        \n        # Determine image name\n        image_name = metadata.agent_name\n        tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n        \n        # Build the image\n        build_result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n            dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n            context_path=workspace_path,\n            image_name=image_name,\n            tag=tag,\n            build_args=build_args,\n        )\n        \n        return build_result\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. PublishRuntime Integration\n\nThe `PublishRuntime` uses `DockerService` for image preparation:\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for publishing agents.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n    \n    def _prepare_local_image(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        options: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare local image for publishing.\"\"\"\n        image_name = metadata.agent_name\n        \n        # Get image info to verify it exists\n        try:\n            info = self.docker_service.get_image_info(image_name)\n            self.logger.info(f\"Found local image: {info['id']}\")\n        except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n            raise ValueError(\n                f\"Image {image_name} not found. Run 'build' first.\"\n            )\n        \n        # Push to registry if credentials provided\n        if options.get(\"image_url\"):\n            push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n                image_name=image_name,\n                registry_url=options.get(\"image_url\"),\n                username=options.get(\"image_username\"),\n                password=options.get(\"image_password\"),\n            )\n            return push_result[\"pushed_image\"]\n        \n        return image_name\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Models\n\n### Build Result Schema\n\n```python\n{\n    \"image_name\": str,       # Full image name with tag (e.g., \"my-agent:v1.0.0\")\n    \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (e.g., \"sha256:abc123...\")\n    \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.5 MB\")\n    \"build_time\": str,       # Duration string (e.g., \"15.3s\")\n}\n```\n\n### Push Result Schema\n\n```python\n{\n    \"pushed_image\": str,     # Full image name in registry\n    \"push_time\": str,        # ISO 8601 timestamp\n    \"registry\": str,         # Registry URL used\n}\n```\n\n### Image Info Schema\n\n```python\n{\n    \"id\": str,               # Docker image ID\n    \"size\": str,             # Human-readable size\n    \"created\": str,          # Creation timestamp\n    \"tags\": List[str],       # List of image tags\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Exception | Description |\n|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| Docker Unavailable | `RuntimeError` | Docker daemon not accessible |\n| Build Failed | `docker.errors.BuildError` | Image build failure |\n| Image Not Found | `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | Image doesn't exist |\n| Push Failed | `RuntimeError` | Registry push failure |\n| API Error | `docker.errors.APIError` | Docker API error |\n| Login Failed | `docker.errors.APIError` | Registry authentication failure |\n\n### Error Patterns\n\n**Docker Availability Check:**\n```python\nif not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n```\n\n**Build Error Handling:**\n```python\ntry:\n    result = self.docker_service.build_image(...)\nexcept docker.errors.BuildError as e:\n    # Log build output for debugging\n    if self.verbose:\n        for log in e.build_log:\n            if 'error' in log:\n                self.logger.error(log['error'])\n    raise RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}\")\n```\n\n**Image Not Found:**\n```python\ntry:\n    info = self.docker_service.get_image_info(image_name)\nexcept docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n    raise ValueError(f\"Image {image_name} not found. Run 'build' first.\")\n```\n\n**Non-blocking Removal:**\n```python\n# remove_image returns bool, doesn't raise\nsuccess = self.docker_service.remove_image(image_name)\nif not success:\n    self.logger.warning(f\"Could not remove image {image_name}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Used For |\n|----------|----------|\n| `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket/address |\n| `DOCKER_TLS_VERIFY` | Enable TLS verification |\n| `DOCKER_CERT_PATH` | Path to TLS certificates |\n| `HTTP_PROXY` / `HTTPS_PROXY` | Proxy for registry operations |\n| `NO_PROXY` | Comma-separated list of hosts to bypass proxy |\n\n### Docker Client Configuration\n\nThe Docker client is initialized lazily using `docker.from_env()` which reads:\n- Environment variables (DOCKER_HOST, etc.)\n- Docker config file (~/.docker/config.json)\n- System defaults\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **DockerService tests**:\n   - `test_check_docker_available_success` - Docker daemon accessible\n   - `test_check_docker_available_failure` - Docker daemon unavailable\n   - `test_build_image_success` - Successful image build\n   - `test_build_image_failure` - Build error handling\n   - `test_get_image_info` - Image inspection\n   - `test_format_size` - Size formatting for various byte values\n   - `test_push_image_success` - Successful push\n   - `test_push_image_with_auth` - Push with credentials\n   - `test_remove_image_success` - Successful removal\n   - `test_remove_image_not_found` - Non-existent image handling\n\n2. **Integration with Runtime tests**:\n   - `test_build_local_uses_docker_service` - BuildRuntime integration\n   - `test_publish_prepares_image` - PublishRuntime integration\n\n### Mock Strategy\n\n```python\n# Mock Docker client for unit tests\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker_client():\n    with patch('docker.from_env') as mock_from_env:\n        client = MagicMock()\n        mock_from_env.return_value = client\n        yield client\n\ndef test_build_image_success(mock_docker_client):\n    # Setup mock\n    mock_image = MagicMock()\n    mock_image.id = \"sha256:abc123\"\n    mock_image.attrs = {'Size': 131072000}\n    mock_image.tags = [\"test:latest\"]\n    \n    mock_docker_client.images.build.return_value = (\n        mock_image,\n        [{'stream': 'Step 1/5'}, {'stream': 'Successfully built'}]\n    )\n    mock_docker_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n    \n    # Test\n    service = DockerService(verbose=False)\n    result = service.build_image(\n        dockerfile_path=Path(\"Dockerfile\"),\n        context_path=Path(\".\"),\n        image_name=\"test\",\n        tag=\"latest\",\n    )\n    \n    # Assert\n    assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test:latest\"\n    assert result[\"image_size\"] == \"125.0 MB\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **Docker Operations E2E**:\n   - Build simple Python agent image\n   - Push to local registry (if available)\n   - Verify image info retrieval\n   - Cleanup/remove image\n\n2. **Error Scenarios**:\n   - Docker daemon not running\n   - Invalid Dockerfile syntax\n   - Registry authentication failure\n   - Network timeout during push\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Registry Credentials**:\n   - Credentials passed via parameters, never logged\n   - Docker SDK handles credential storage securely\n   - Support for credential helpers (~/.docker/config.json)\n\n2. **Image Security**:\n   - Build context is limited to workspace directory\n   - No sensitive files should be in build context\n   - .dockerignore support for excluding files\n\n3. **Network Security**:\n   - HTTPS for registry operations\n   - TLS verification for Docker daemon\n   - Proxy support for corporate environments\n\n4. **Resource Limits**:\n   - Consider memory limits for build operations\n   - Build timeout handling\n   - Concurrent build limitations\n\n---\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n|-----------|------------------|-------|\n| Docker availability check | <100ms | Ping operation |\n| Image build | 10s - 5min | Depends on image size and layers |\n| Image info retrieval | <100ms | Local Docker operation |\n| Image push | 10s - 5min | Depends on image size and network |\n| Image removal | <1s | Local operation |\n\n### Optimization Strategies\n\n1. **Layer Caching**: Leverage Docker layer caching for faster rebuilds\n2. **Parallel Operations**: Build/push operations can be parallelized\n3. **Progress Streaming**: Stream logs for better UX on long operations\n4. **Image Pruning**: Cleanup intermediate images to save disk space\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK for Python |\n| `requests` | >=2.25.0 | HTTP library (Docker SDK dependency) |\n| `urllib3` | >=1.26.0 | HTTP client (Docker SDK dependency) |\n\n### Python Requirements\n\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    # ... other deps\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **BuildKit Support**: Use BuildKit for advanced build features\n2. **Multi-platform Builds**: Support for cross-platform image builds\n3. **Build Cache Export**: Export/import build cache for CI/CD\n4. **Image Scanning**: Integration with vulnerability scanners\n5. **Parallel Builds**: Build multiple images concurrently\n6. **Build Metrics**: Detailed timing and resource usage metrics\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n- [Docker SDK for Python](https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/) - Official SDK docs\n- [Docker Engine API](https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/) - REST API reference\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775895394313,"end":1775895394323}}}}
